            <div1 id="d4" type="poem">
                <pb entity="DSSR_000002671_0001" n="107"/>
                <head>WINTER IN THE SIERRAS</head>

                <p>BY MARY AUSTIN<lb/> &mdash; </p>

                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l rend="center">T<hi rend="small-caps">HE</hi> pines are black on Sierra's
                        slope, </l>
                    <l rend="center">And white are the drifted snows; </l>
                    <l rend="center">The flowers are gone, the buckthorn bare, </l>
                    <l rend="center">And chilly the north wind blows. </l>
                    <l rend="center">The pine-boughs creak, </l>
                    <l rend="center">And the pine-trees speak </l>
                    <l rend="center">A language the north wind knows. </l>
                </lg>

                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l rend="center">There's never a track leads in or out </l>
                    <l rend="center">Of the cave of the big brown bear; </l>
                    <l rend="center">The squirrels have hid in their deepest holes, </l>
                    <l rend="center">And fastened the doors with care. </l>
                    <l rend="center">The red fox prowls, </l>
                    <l rend="center">And the lean wolf howls </l>
                    <l rend="center">As he hunts far down from the lair. </l>
                </lg>

                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l rend="center">The eagle hangs on the wing all day, </l>
                    <l rend="center">On the chance of a single kill; </l>
                    <l rend="center">The little gray hawk hunts far and wide </l>
                    <l rend="center">Before he can get his fell. </l>
                    <l rend="center">The snow-wreaths sift, </l>
                    <l rend="center">And the blown snows drift </l>
                    <l rend="center">To the canyons deep and still. </l>
                </lg>



            </div1>


        </body>
